        <hr noshade size="2" color="#545A7D">
        
         Depends on your playstyle. If you group more than solo, bump mana, more of a mana pool = one more twitch when everything is going to Hell. If you solo, your mana pool is fairly immaterial in danger situations, coz you will time yourself on your own mana pool.</P><P>In a party situation, you will run out of mana fast in dangerous situations. In a solo situation, if everything goes FUBAR, you will hit the dirt with FD and /q out.</P><P>I go for alot of mana gear, my mana easily is 2x my HP. I'm not a twitch bitch, but I know sometimes a twitch at the right time has saved the group.</P><P>I rarely solo, so this is "the mostly grouping necro's opinion".</P><P>BTW ... I hope I'm not going to get flamed over advocating twitching in this post. The point about twitching is it depends on who is calling the shots. I twitch when I feel like it, I never send myself OOM over twitching unless I absolutely need to (cleric OOM, bard tanking and tanks dead ...)</P><P>I have big issues when a guild asks me to be twitching all a raid simply coz they feel I have no other use. One guild did that to their 6 necros, who I believe, a fair few have left for being treated as no more than "twitch bitches".</P><P>I twitch when I feel like it. That's that, and I twitch when I need to. Just, more mana allows me to be more flexible when I need to, and generally, be an emergency power source so the group don't wipe.</P><P>Saminga Amaranth, 60th Bad Girl, not 60th Twitch Bitch of Avatars of Discord, Rodcet Nife.</P><P>Good girls go to Heaven, bad girls FD and /q out.<a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
