        <hr noshade size="2" color="#545A7D">
        
         First, understand that maxing int does not neccesarily max mana.  There is lots of nice equipment that gives plus hp and plus mana with little or no int gain.  Take a BS necklace...the mana gain for it is better than a plus 10 int necklace if your int is over 200.  Plus you get plus 65 hp. </P><P>My gear is far from perfect and my int started low for a DE.  When I made Ish, the thought was that dex helped you channel thru stufff, so I gave myself some extra dex.  LOL!!!  Even so, my current gear gives me about 3200 mana and about 2100 HP, self buffed.  HP matter more than the mana.  But you can easily have both.</P><P><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=157918" target=new>Ishtarra Gemeinseele </a><BR>Warlock of the Dirty Soul<BR>Uber N00b Extraordinaire<BR>Tunare Server<a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
