        <hr noshade size="2" color="#545A7D">
        
         int from 201-255 = ~324 mana<BR>arch lich 53hp (not counting PvP code) = 35 mana<BR>demi lich 48hp (not counting PvP code) = 31 mana<BR>lich 32hp (not counting PvP code.....) = 20 mana</P><P>so lets say you have over 200 int...you have an item with 6 int and another with 35 HP.  the 6 int = ~36 mana, and the 35hp = 35, 31, or 20 mana (with PvP code being counted into HP loss).</P><P>i say stick around 200ish int and go for HP after that.  but that is jsut me.</P><P><a href="http://www.theinverselogic.com/" target="_blank"><BR>Abillister "Monkey" Abu<BR>Inverse Logic</a><a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
